---
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting"
  description="Consulting, workshops and talks on deliberate AI use, AI literacy and Human-AI Interaction in organizations."
>
  <section class="page-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Consulting</p>
        <h1>
          Consulting, workshops and talks on using AI more deliberately in organizations.
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p>
        I help organizations and teams understand how to use AI in everyday work - not
        only through better prompts, but through clearer principles, verification habits,
        responsibility, data awareness and human-AI workflows.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="consulting-stack">
      <div class="consulting-intro prose">
        <p>
          This is not a tool demo or a list of ChatGPT tricks. The focus is how people
          actually use AI: when they trust it, when they stop checking, what they put
          into tools, who signs off on the result and how AI changes the way a team works.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section class="consulting-section" aria-labelledby="help-title">
        <div class="section-header compact-section-header">
          <div>
            <p class="section-kicker">Offer</p>
            <h2 id="help-title">What I help with</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            Practical, research-informed support for teams that already use AI or are
            preparing shared principles for generative tools.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="service-grid">
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>structuring AI use in teams</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>AI literacy for organizations</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>workshops on trust, verification and responsibility</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>reviewing how a team uses generative tools</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>creating simple principles for what can be used, checked or avoided</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>helping leaders discuss AI, decisions and accountability</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check" /><span>AI in communication, education, culture and creative work</span></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="consulting-section" aria-labelledby="situations-title">
        <div class="section-header compact-section-header">
          <div>
            <p class="section-kicker">Typical situations</p>
            <h2 id="situations-title">When this work is useful</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            The most common problem is not a lack of prompts. It is unclear judgment,
            unclear responsibility and inconsistent use across a team.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="scenario-list">
          <li>A team uses AI, but everyone uses it differently.</li>
          <li>The organization wants to use AI, but has no shared rules.</li>
          <li>Leaders are not sure which tasks can safely be supported by AI.</li>
          <li>People paste sensitive information into tools without understanding the risk.</li>
          <li>AI speeds up writing, but nobody knows who is responsible for the final text.</li>
          <li>The team needs training that is not just a list of prompts.</li>
          <li>The organization wants internal principles for using generative AI.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="consulting-columns">
        <section class="panel" aria-labelledby="best-fit-title">
          <h2 id="best-fit-title">Best fit</h2>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>leadership teams</li>
            <li>communication / marketing / content teams</li>
            <li>HR / L&amp;D</li>
            <li>education and cultural institutions</li>
            <li>creative teams</li>
            <li>organizations preparing internal AI guidelines</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="panel" aria-labelledby="formats-title">
          <h2 id="formats-title">Formats</h2>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>expert briefing</li>
            <li>workshop</li>
            <li>advisory session</li>
            <li>talk / lecture</li>
            <li>review of current AI use</li>
            <li>internal AI use principles session</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>

      <section class="consulting-section" aria-labelledby="session-title">
        <div class="section-header compact-section-header">
          <div>
            <p class="section-kicker">Process</p>
            <h2 id="session-title">How a session can work</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            The format can stay compact, but it should connect AI literacy with the real
            tasks, risks and decision points of the team.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ol class="process-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Context</strong>
            <p>how the team currently uses AI</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Use cases and risks</strong>
            <p>where AI helps and where it needs caution</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Human-AI workflow</strong>
            <p>where AI enters the process</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Practical principles</strong>
            <p>what can be used, checked or avoided</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Next steps</strong>
            <p>how to keep AI use meaningful after the session</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="panel consulting-note" aria-labelledby="not-title">
        <h2 id="not-title">What this is not</h2>
        <p>
          This is not legal advice, clinical advice or a tool demo focused only on prompts.
          The focus is the human side of AI use: judgment, trust, communication,
          responsibility and the way teams actually work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="contact-band consulting-cta" aria-labelledby="consulting-contact-title">
        <p class="small-label" id="consulting-contact-title">Contact</p>
        <p>Contact for consulting, workshops or talks.</p>
        <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
